<br>
We plan to start a new guild here, but would like to see if anyone is interested before we found it. We do have a website (under construcion) at www.guildportal.com (name of guild is The Hideout until we find a better name).<br>
<br>
We imagine our guild as a group of people who question and challenge the boundries of society. They will be outcasts/outlaws, choosing to follow only a vew groundrules but otherwise they strive to be free to think for themselves. <br>
<br>
It is a guild for casual players as well as regular players, as we hope to become a group of friends that have fun together. We will NOT be a raiding guild, so if you like raiding you’d probably be better off in another guild. We are trying to create a home for kindred spirits out there, who feel there is more to Norrath than just constantly hunt for experience, money and items.<br>
<br>
In our former guild we had events like the Neriak Championships, various races (umm yes some drunken ones too…), parties, hide and seeks, parties, Sightseeing in Neriak, parties… <br>
<br>
Note that all members of our guild are expected to stay in character at all times, and that we allow all races and classes as long as they are free spirits like ourselves.<br>
<br>
I hope we will get enough people interested to get the guild going. Our goal is not to expand and keep recruiting members, but rather to start the guild and let everyone get to know eachother better. <br>
<br>
I am writing a journal in the forum A Bard for a Day if you wish to know more about me.<br>
<br>
Sincerely yours, Ninylien (conjurer)<br>
